messages.original: I'm having issues with the map, so I've just removed the missile paths.   3 groups of Kh-101s are flying to Ozerne, Zhytomyr Oblast from the northeast.  6 groups of Kh-101s are flying to southern Ternopil Oblast.  2 Kh-101s were shot down on approach to Kyiv‚Ä¶

Correction: The 2 Kh-101s flying to Kyiv from the east were shot down. 
The ones flying to the city from the south are flying to Ozerne, Zhytomyr Oblast.
No changes to the 6 groups of Kh-101s (~24 missiles in total). 
The kalibr group (2-3 missiles) is flying to Ozerne from the south.
The first four Kh-101s approach Zhytomyr-Ozerne. Possibly going to strike the airbase.
The first four Kh-101s approach Zhytomyr-Ozerne. Possibly going to strike the airbase.
Explosions. 2-3 more flying in from the south.
Explosions. 2-3 more flying in from the south.
Repeated explosions were heard in Zhytomyr

Updated map.
The remaining (~24) Kh-101 cruise missiles are flying through the western regions of Ukraine. 
~16 missiles flying in 4 groups one after another are heading towards Ternopil City. 
~8 missiles are bypassing Khmelnytskyi City from the north.
I also missed ~2 Kh-101 impacts in Vasylkiv, Kyiv Oblast.
Explosions in Vinnytsia. Likely Kh-101 impacts.
The remaining Kh-101 cruise missiles are flying to Burshtyn, Ivano-Frankivsk Oblast from two directions.

2 groups of Kh-101s are flying to Lviv City from the east and southeast.
2 groups of Kh-101s are flying to Burshtyn, Ivano-Frankivsk Oblast.
Explosions in Kalush, Ivano-Frankivsk Oblast. Kh-101 impacts.
Missiles flying to Lviv disappeared, likely impacting the Drohobych area. As of now, the airspace seems to be clear of missiles.

The Polish Armed Forces published a statement calling the breach of their airspace by Russian Geran-2 drones an "unprecedented act of aggression that posed a real threat to the safety" of Polish citizens. 
They stated that their air defence, with the help of Polish and allied radar systems, tracked and shot down multiple drones. Efforts are now ongoing to locate drone debris.
Missiles flying to Lviv disappeared, likely impacting the Drohobych area. As of now, the airspace seems to be clear of missiles.

A minimum of 36 Russian cruise missiles (32 Kh-101s and 4 Kalibrs) were used in the attack on Ukraine today. Interception rates are unknown, but 3 missiles are confirmed to have been shot down. 
Targets were hit in Kyiv, Ivano-Frankivsk, Zhytomyr, Vinnytsia and Lviv Oblasts.
More details on the consequences will be posted later.
Because of the Polish air defence activities, I have a feeling the Ukrainian Airforce is going to come up with an even more ridiculous claim about interception rates than usual.

Scenes from Zhytomyr City after it was hit by several Kalibr and Kh-101 cruise missiles this morning. The first image shows four impacts. The targets remain unknown, but interestingly, it doesn't appear Ozerne Airbase was hit.

A large fire is burning in Vinnytsia City after it was hit by 1-2 Kh-101 cruise missiles this morning. What exactly was hit is currently unknown, but we may get FIRMS data showing active fires.
